Cognitive Builder CourseUnleash the Power of WatsonAre you building smart applications? Get expert instruction on the skills needed to prototype, integrate and deploy cognitive technologies and create intelligent products in this fully online class.
Buy NowCost$̶7̶5̶0̶ $399Use Discount Code "CogBuilderLaunch"Length4-5 Weeks24-28 hours self-paced onlineFormatOnline LearningSelf-paced with the option to interact with instructor to ask questions and get helpThis course focuses on integrating machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) into your software development environment. Some python experience is required.
Become a next-level application builder with the Cognitive Builder Course from GalvanizeThere is tremendous opportunity for professionals in the IT industry. But it is also easy to be lost in the crowd. It is the credentials held by an IT Professional that can be the determining factor of recognition and success. IBM Professional Certification offers credentials for successful IT Professionals across the industry.
IBM Professional Certification is available in all areas of the business, including IBM Analytics, IBM Cloud, IBM Security, and IBM Watson technology.
As successful participant in the Cognitive Builder Course, you will be issued a IBM Certified Watson Cognitive Developer certification by IBM. This certification will be recorded in your IBM Professional Certification Marketplace and will enable the participant to digitally advertise their certification.
Not sure if this is the right course for you?Explore our part-time courses which include Data Science Fundamentals and Spark for Data Science.
Part-time CoursesCognitive Builder Course OverviewBecome a next-level application builder with the Cognitive Builder course from IBM Watson & Galvanize. This hands-on course teaches developers how to prototype, integrate and deploy cognitive technologies and create intelligent products utilizing IBM's Watson Developer Cloud.
Play VideoAbout the InstructorJean-Francois (Jeff) OmhoverInstructor, Sr Data Scientist
Innovative computer scientist with more than a decade of experience researching and teaching at a leading French engineering school. Empowerment driven instructor for PhD, graduate and undergraduate level students, with one foot always in the field.
LinkedInWhat You Will LearnModule 1Introduction to Cognitive Technologies
What is Machine Learning?Main components of BlueMix / WatsonUsing ToneAnalyzer to detect emotions in natural languageUsing VisualRecognition to classify images
Module 2Cognitive Technologies & Business
Opportunities offered by Cognitive TechnologiesDesigning an Intelligent productMining insights using DiscoveryDesigning a conversational agent using Conversation
Module 3Cognitive Design Roles
Solving a business problems with intelligent technologiesIntelligent system architectureDeployment phase concerns and how to solve them
Module 4Develop a prototype
Development processes for intelligent products and systemsDeveloping a prototype based on ML/AI functionalitiesAssembling components of the Bluemix Platform
